('additional-maths:1-4-linear-and-quadratic-inequalities:tips:a543e0ff', 'additional-maths', 'additional-maths:1-4-linear-and-quadratic-inequalities', '1.4 Linear and Quadratic Inequalities', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "explain — Present the solution set clearly", "reading": "<p>Communication marks are lost on presentation, not maths.</p><p>Use \"<strong>or</strong>\" for a two-part answer (\\( x < -2 \\) or \\( x > 3 \\)) and \"<strong>and</strong>\"/a single chain for a between-answer (\\( -2 \\le x \\le 3 \\)). On a number line, make circles unmistakably <strong>open</strong> (strict) or <strong>closed</strong> (non-strict) — OCR 2019 Q2b penalised ambiguous circles.</p>", "question": "Which is the correct way to write the solution of \\( x^2 - x - 6 > 0 \\)?", "options": ["\\( -2 > x > 3 \\)", "\\( x < -2 \\) or \\( x > 3 \\)", "\\( -2 < x < 3 \\)", "\\( x < -2 \\) and \\( x > 3 \\)"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "The two separate arms are joined by ''or''; \\( -2 > x > 3 \\) is impossible and ''and'' would describe no values."}'::jsonb),
